The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Johl, Kahlon tied at 25th

Hainan Island (China): India?s Amandeep Johl and Harmeet Kahlon shot five-under 67 each to be tied 25th on the opening day of the TCL Classic golf tournament on Thursday. 

Englishman Paul Casey, Swedish duo of Fredrik Andersson Hed and Johan Edfors, and Chawalit Plaphol of Thailand emerged as joint first round leaders at eight-under 64 at the Yalong Bay golf club. 

A stroke behind the four were as many as 10 players at seven-under, and another 10 at six-under. 

Among other Indians in fray, Jeev Milkha Singh brought in a card of three-under 69 for a tied 62nd place and Shiv Kapur had a one-under 71 to be tied 110th, while Jyoti Randhawa with a par round was tied 126th. 

Rafique leads 

City-based Rafique Ali overshadowed his compatriot S.S.P. Chowrasia to take the lead on the first day of the Rs 10 lakh Hero Golf Chandigarh Open at the Chandigarh Golf Club on Thursday, adds another report from Chandigarh. 

